After 716. HISTORIA ABBATUM.

This must be later than 716 as it narrates the death of Ceolfrid and the election of Hwaetbert in that year. From the fact that nothing is narrated after that date it would not be safe to argue that it must have been written soon after 716, as Bede might naturally feel a delicaey in writing about the administration of Hwaet- bert, who, as we saw (p. xiv), overlived him.

After 716. IN MARCUM.

This was written after the In Samuelem, Opp. x. 37, which, as we have seen, was written in 716. The In Luc-am had been written ‘ante annos plurimos.' Ib. 3. Probably, therefore, it is some time later than 716.
